The Dominion of Newfoundland, officially simply Newfoundland, was a self-governing dominion of the British Empire that existed between 1907 and 1922. For the remaining two years of its existence, Governor and future President Charles Alexander Harris served as regent in the absence of a monarch. It was succeeded by the Republic of Newfoundland in 1922.
